{
  "text": "Warning signs that should result in increased attention are the absence of meconium passage, early occurrences of constipation, an empty rectal ampulla, refractory constipation, etc. Disturbing neurological signs include motor and sensory dysfunction in the lower extremities, abnormal reflex activity and anorectal sensation. An MRI of the spinal cord is justified in these cases [CITATION_1] .",
